OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FLeisure chain cuts hours as
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fenergy bills triple        
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A leisure centre chain has said the    
OL,6, rising cost of living is forcing it to 
OL,7, reduce its opening hours with a        
OL,8, "temporary winter programme".          
OL,10,FBetter Leisure, which runs 268 centres 
OL,11,Facross the UK, said its energy costs   
OL,12,Fhad more than tripled since 2019.      
OL,14,FThe charitable social enterprise said  
OL,15,Fit was not sustainable after the       
OL,16,F"recent struggles" of the pandemic.    
OL,18,FParent company GLL said the            
OL,19,F"extraordinary" programme would affect 
OL,20,Fmore than 200 of its centres.          
